<quantity id="4CBA9B30860D6B2BFDF08F66FD0FFCA2" box="[552,661,786,825]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="94" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
west of 'Marohn' homestead, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30860D6B2BFF388F35FEA5FCFC" box="[224,319,833,871]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="94" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
south-west of Gundy, NSW (Locality 28).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860D6B2BFEC98F1AFCCEFC5F" blockId="31.[223,1207,415,1333]" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">Stratigraphic position. In bioclastic limestone, upper part of the Dangarfield Formation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860D6B2BFEC98FBFFBA0FC69" blockId="31.[223,1207,415,1333]" box="[273,1082,971,1010]" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">
Geographic distribution. 
<typeStatus id="54F98877860D6B2BFD328FBFFCA5FC69" box="[746,831,971,1010]" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">Type</typeStatus>
locality only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860D6B2BFEC88F8DFCEFFBBA" blockId="31.[223,1207,415,1333]" box="[272,885,1017,1057]" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">Geological age. Late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860D6B2BFED7885CFE50FBE6" blockId="31.[223,1207,415,1333]" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">
Etymology. Referring to the township of Gundy, 
<collectingRegion id="4986F837860D6B2BFBBF885CFE5FFBE6" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860D6B2BFED788F1FB85FAAE" blockId="31.[223,1207,415,1333]" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">
Remarks. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860D6B2BFC6A88F1FBB4FB30" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[946,1070,1157,1195]" class="Gastropoda" family="Elasmonematidae" genus="Kimina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="31" pageNumber="94" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860D6B2BFC6A88F1FBB4FB30" box="[946,1070,1157,1195]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">Kimina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., in having smooth convex whorls with deviated protoconch, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860D6B2BFEF78895FE36FA9C" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[303,428,1249,1287]" class="Gastropoda" family="Elasmonematidae" genus="Kimina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="31" pageNumber="94" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860D6B2BFEF78895FE36FA9C" box="[303,428,1249,1287]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="94">Kimina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. has a moderate umbilicus and more convex whorls with opisthocline growth lines.
</paragraph>
